<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">I don't have a matching LDON story, but your entire tale sounds familiar.  Throughout the last five years, enchanters have tended to group with lower-level groups and clerics have tended to group with higher-level groups.  It might not seem fair, but that's the way it has to be.  We just do much better in terms of resists and aggro when we're fighting low-blues.  Clerics don't have to worry about resists at all (heals and buffs always work) and the amount of aggro they get is strictly limited to the amount of healing needed, so a higher-level group actually makes their job a little easier.
<br />

<br />
Paladin aggro is all about low-mana stuns, no doubt about it.  They need to keep stunning, even if it reduces their dps.
<br />

<br />
As for the spellcasters... yeah, they've gotten meaner in recent weeks.  It used to be that spellcasters (in all zones) didn't cast quite so much.  Now they sometimes chain-nuke.  Sometimes that's ok -- most mobs do less damage with spells than they would with melee, plus it gives you time to cast a spell without being interrupted.  But a slowed wizard mob does a lot more damage by spell, and can dispel buffs, root, and stun as well... it becomes a real pain.  There's also the surprise factor -- the cleric may be casting a slow heal on you because you're only at 60% health, then that ice comet hits and you go from 60% to dead instantly.  Oops!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
