<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="name"><a name="91660"></a></span><span class="postdetails">#8:&nbsp;<font color=black><b></b> Author:&nbsp;<b>Alcina Moonsong</b>,&nbsp;</font></span><span class="postdetails"><font color=black></font></span>
<a href="viewtopic.php?p=91660#91660"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails"><font color=black>Posted: Mon Jan 03, 2005 3:54 pm</font><span class="gen"><br>
</td></tr>
<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">I don't have a story like that either, but it does sound familiar. Over my last 6 years playing though, I've learned a lot of tricks. Pallies make assume tanks now. I'd say in the last year, me and some friends have pretty much created a wonderful group. We always group with my level 66 enchanter, a 66 warrior, 66 Pally, 66 mage, my 66 cleric and fill the last spot with another guildy, anywhere from our 62 shammy to the 61 ranger or 66 monk. We did BoT last night with the shammy. We've gotten it down rather perfect though, if we end up with more than one mob, my enchanter will mez it, then before breaking the mez, the Pally will cast a few stuns on it to get agro. It works 99% of the time. Also, when the pally is tanking, I can tash when the mob is still at 100% and slow right after because he'll stun for agro. Very seldom will my enchanter get agro from a mob this way. Now if we don't have the pally, and the warrior is the main tank, I'll wait to 90% to tash, and about 85% to slow. 
<br />

<br />
I can tell you that with 2 boxing a cleric, the faster you can get the slow off, the better. Of course, another thing that might help not get agro is that my enchanter has had a horse since that expansion came out, so she doesn't have to actually sit after casting anything. The other thing is at the higher end, you can't wait until 50% to slow a lot of mobs or they'll eat your tank and your cleric might not be able to heal them fast enough. 
<br />

<br />
I think the last thing I'll add about this is that I also learned to check to see if I need tash. If I get resisted on a few mobs the first time in a zone, I'll tash before trying to slow. If you keep casting slow on a mob and it resists then you will gain agro. If you tash first then slow, you have a smaller chance of not getting agro if you have a good tank. 
<br />

<br />
I've played almost every class in the game now, and each has it's advantage, just pay attention to what works for what class, and if someone isn't doing something, politely point out how they could possibly make it better. A lot of people will take advice and at least try it once. Lol I taught the pally how to use my chanter for pulls with Pacification so he only gets one mob at a time, when the pally was around lvl 64. He'd never knew to do that before, now he won't pull without Pacification unless he has to.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
