<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">Lull and pull is easy for low level paladins. Your group was using the wrong strategy to pull. The paladins don't pacify after 60 though, since their spells cap at 55 for that line. You can paci after 55 for them, just have them target and you /assist and cast. It's best to assist so you don't get accidental aggro. I won't get into chanter tanking <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="icon_razz.gif" border="0" /> 
<br />

<br />
The monk was having aggro lingering problems, that's common since they nerfed FD splitting. The problems monks have is they can't help fight the mobs much anymore. Once they get up they bring everything with them. Those monks and rangers always stealing aggro from their procs, it's a group,, monk should use non-proc(hands) to help the paladin(tank) if need be (I would be crying about then).
<br />

<br />
Pally lull and pull, mmm easy. Ykesha weapons have a stun proc, your pally must have had issues with gear. Cease and Desist is aggro dominance coupled with great pulling spells too. Flash of what??, not in LDON unless you have a deathwish. Pally lull, pally cease, pally aggro magnet, monk DPS, bst DPS, chanter DPS, cleric DPS, happy group. Clerics get lots of aggro if they cast nukes. Casters love chanter groups(wizards/magicians=major ownage). Tash is great for magic based nukes, YeaH!!
<br />

<br />
I get the part of you being lowest level but clerics can paci /assist also if its a hard one and you want the great exp. It helps if the cleric or chanter is one of the highest in the group for paci pulling hard ldon. Oh and be sure to Charisma buff the cleric/pally if they are doing the paci spells. Charisma is a major boost at 100, 200, 300 stats. That helps if paci fails and a check for charisma is made for aggro on failure. Heck even monks can cast paci anymore, though it's only good for one target.
<br />

<br />
Monks pull best in EC and NRO ldon. The flying monkies make good charm pets, MAJOR DPS and really are great for those wandering mind type spells <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" />). Monkies meaning the mobs in Everfrost ldon, hehe. If you desire a master aggro tank then grab a shadow knight. They aggro from the other side of the zone. 
<br />

<br />
Sometimes it helps to just slow and nothing else but buff the group. Beastlords are my favorites when they slow for me <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />)!! Chanters are the best pullers in Sro LDON and normal is like hard in comparison to the others. Stun, I never used it, chain cast MEZ works for me or just aoe mesmerization and let my group bail me out. Stun has its uses sometimes. Low level mezz just as good to level 55 anyway. Umm,, you should Tash, Slow, and then contemplate anything else, ALWAYS!!
<br />

<br />
One word "mesmerization" is a chanter research spell level 16 targeted aoe that is the funnest thing when you are so young and full of energy <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="icon_razz.gif" border="0" />. Just target the puller and everything nearby is "mez". Just don't do it nearby any ldon "chest/trap/box ".
<br />
<a href="http://www.allakhazam.com/db/spell.html?spell=307" target="_blank">http://www.allakhazam.com/db/spell.html?spell=307</a>
<br />

<br />
You should make your *cycle target next npc and *cycle last target keys. Those are assignable in the options keyboard menu but don't have a default value. It helps for single target tash and slow or mez. I get sick when I see time equipped players that use mouse targetting *blah*</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
